<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">389. Haring, Elda. Color for Your Yard and Garden. New York: Hawthome,1971. 240 pp. Index, B/W illus., color illus. </p><p class="annot">Two-thirds of this text is devoted to a plant spectrum -- from yellowto orange, pink to rose, red, blue to purple, white and green -- with plant lists, illustrations, and information on their characteristics. Colors throughout the year are the subject of a brief section of essays, illustrated by timeless photographs that portray the spectrum. The introduction is by garden authority Helen Van Pelt. </p></div>
